==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tarpum
<hw>Tar"pum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
very large marine fish (<spn>Megapolis Atlanticus</spn>) of the Southern
United States and the West Indies. It often becomes six or more feet in
length, and has large silvery scales. The scales are a staple article of
trade, and are used in fancywork. Called also <altname>tarpon</altname>,
<altname>sabalo</altname>, <altname>savanilla</altname>,
<altname>silverfish</altname>, and <altname>jewfish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarquinish</ent>⟦br⟧
